---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import fishImg from '../images/anglerfish.png';
import waterImg from '../images/water-reflections.jpg';
import fishBallImg from '../images/fish-ball.png';
import cave1Img from '../images/cave1.png';
---



<section class="fish-hero overflow-hidden pt-32 pb-20 w-full mx-auto relative flex px-8 justify-center flex-col bg-green-950">
    <!-- <span class="bg-gradient-to-tr from-fuchsia-400 via-purple-800 to-indigo-950 fixed top-0 left-0 mix-blend-difference top-0 left-0 w-full h-full z-30"></span> -->
    <div class="fish-hero__container">
        <div class="fish-hero__content relative w-auto mx-auto pt-2">
            <span class="bg-black w-full relative bg-opacity-50 rounded-t-2xl text-white pl-8 flex items-start justify-end">
                <span class="z-40 mix-blend-difference">
                    <span class="font-bayon text-lg tracking-widest mr-1 self-start mix-blend-hard-light text-shadow">protect a monster from the </span>
                    <span class="font-kings leading-none z-40 mix-blend-difference mr-2 filter text-shadow" id="fish-midnight">midnight zone</span>
                    <!-- <span class="font-kings mix-blend-hard-light text-shadow" id="fish-zone">zone</span> -->
                    <!-- <span class="font-bayon text-2xl tracking-widest mix-blend-hard-light text-shadow">monster</span> -->
                </span>
            </span>            
            <div class="relative z-30">
                <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full bg-black z-30 opacity-60 mix-blend-difference"></div>
                <Image src={fishImg} alt="Anglerfish" class="fish-hero__image fish-shadow w-full z-40 mix-blend-difference h-full object-cover relative block" />
                <div class="fishball animation-fishball absolute z-30">
                    <Image src={fishBallImg} alt="Sigil" class="fish-hero__ball object-contain" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <span class="bg-gradient-to-tr from-fuchsia-700 via-violet-900 to-purple-950 absolute top-0 left-0 mix-blend-difference top-0 left-0 w-full h-full z-50"></span>
            <!-- <span class="absolute bg-teal-500 top-0 left-0 w-full h-full z-0 mix-blend-color-difference" role="decoration"></span> -->
            <!-- <div class="h-4 relative block overflow-hidden z-50 bg-purple-500 invert">
                <Image src={waterImg} alt="Water reflections" class="fish-hero__water top-0 left-0 w-full block relative h-full object-cover mix-blend-hard-light" />
            </div> -->
            <h2 class="absolute bottom-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/3 translate-y-1/2 z-50">
                
                <!-- <span class="absolute w-full justify-center flex top-0 items-end left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 z-40 text-white  mix-blend-difference"></span> -->
                <!-- <span class="mix-blend-screen absolute top-0 translate-y-1/2 left-0 text-4xl tracking-normal text-red-500 font-bokor monster-text-shadow">the</span> -->
                <span id="fish-monster" class="mix-blend-screen text-red-500 font-bokor monster-text-shadow">anglerfish</span>
            </h2>            
        </div>
    </div>
    <Image src={waterImg} alt="Water reflections" class="fish-hero__water top-0 left-0 absolute h-full object-cover z-0 mix-blend-difference" />
    <div class="relative z-30 prose">
        <div class="mx-auto bg-black bg-opacity-80 text-lime-100 px-8 pb-14 pt-32 rounded-b-3xl">
            <h2 class="text-4xl  mb-4">Rare specimen needs special care</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">Anglerfish live deep in the ocean, amongst inky blackness and crushing pressure. If light simply strikes it, it will cause the tissue to begin to break down. When specimens make their way to the surface, the massive pressure changes often distort the fish into a crude facisimile of it's true form.</p>
            <p>In 2021, an intact and undamaged anglerfish floated it's way onto a Southern California beach. It was destined for the National History Museum of Los Angeles, where for a limited time, it would be scientific and sightseeing superstar.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">This is one of only 30 anglerfish that have made their way into study and exhibition in such pristine condition. They planned a special exhibit to display this mythic creature from beyond our grasp. But there was a problem...</p>
            <p>The angler fish lives so deep in the ocean that it can't survive in live - it's tissue breaks down. The museum needed a way to display the fish in a way that ensure only necessary light struck the specimen, and wanted to track the total light exposure over the lifetime of the exhibit. That's where we came in.</p>

        </div>
  </div>
</section>


<style>
.fish-shadow {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.05rem rgba(0, 150, 0, 0.9));
}
.fishball {
    width: 15vw;
    height: 15vw;
    top: 45%;
    left: 6vw;

}
.animation-fishball {
    animation: fishball 60s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes fishball {
    0% {
        transform: rotate(0deg);
    }
    100% {
        transform: rotate(360deg);
    }
}

.text-shadow {
    text-shadow: 0.03em 0.04em 0.02em rgba(250, 0, 130, 0.6);
}
.monster-text-shadow {
    text-shadow: 0.02em 0.03em 0.05em rgba(200, 0, 0, 0.9);
}
#fish-midnight {
	font-size: 8vw;
    line-height: 0.7;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  #fish-zone {
	font-size: 8vw;
    line-height:0.6;
  }

  #fish-monster {
	font-size: 16vw;
    /* line-height:0.0; */
    /* padding: 0; */
    /* height: 0; */
  }

</style>